casebody.data:
The People, Resp’ts, v. The N. Y., N. H. & H. R. R. Co., App’lt. Appeal from judgment entered after trial at circuit.

E. N. Taft, for app’lt; S. W. Rosendale, for resp’ts.

Per Curiam.

It seems to us that all the questions which are now raised were properly before the court upon the demurrer heretofore interposed and which has been overruled by the court of appeals, and, therefore, the judgment should be affirmed, with costs.

Van Brunt, P. J., O’Brien and Andrews, JJ., concur.
